{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place eggs, yeast, sugar and milk in mixing bowl then warm <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add flour, butter, vanilla and salt then knead <b>3 min\/<b>. Transfer dough to a large bowl, cover with cling film and leave to rise in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 2 hours). Clean mixing bowl.","Towards end of rising time, line 2 baking trays (approx. 40 cm x 35 cm) with baking paper and continue with recipe."]},{"title":"Filling and Assembly","content":["Place blueberries, sugar and flour in mixing bowl then mix <b>2 sec\/\/speed 2<b>.","Transfer risen dough to a floured work surface. Roll out to a rectangle (approx. 30 cm x 45 cm x 5 mm) and cut into 16 equally-sized rectangles.","Spoon an equal amount of blueberry filling into the centre of each dough rectangle. Working with 1 rectangle at a time, pinch all 4 corners together into the middle to encase the filling. Seal well, then lightly roll between hands to shape into round buns. Place buns seam-side down on prepared baking trays leaving space for each bun to rise during baking. Leave buns to rise for 1 hour.","Towards end of this time, preheat oven to 160°C.","Brush egg evenly over buns. Bake for 25 minutes (160°C) or until lightly golden. Transfer to a wire rack and leave to cool completely before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["2 tsp dried instant yeast","2 medium eggs","110 g sugar","100 g milk","370 g strong white bread flour","50 g unsalted butter, soft","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Filling and Assembly","content":["250 g fresh blueberries","70 g sugar","30 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","1 medium egg, lightly beaten, for brushing"]}],"id":"r295188","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-0mVLwpiXOHk\/XZWrvxAKqBI\/AAAAAAAAfsM\/XVkkrqjfrK0zWBq87zOx77dTub4ZRyy3wCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_thTs_nbtNu_D11ag.png","title":"Blueberry Buns","publishedAt":"2018-02-26T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"765 kJ \/ 182 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking trays (approx. 40 cm x 35 cm), baking paper, cling film, pastry brush, wire rack, rolling pin, large bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["These buns are best eaten the day they are made.","Substitute blueberries with stoned peaches or peeled and deseeded apples, cut into pieces <b>(1 cm).<b>"],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","3h 25m","16 pieces"]}